; Regression test for issue #745: ledger budget: Error: Cannot multiply an amount with a balance
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/745
;
; Previously, running `ledger budget` on a journal where actual postings
; produced a multi-commodity balance under a budgeted parent account caused:
;   "Error: Cannot multiply an amount with a balance"
;
; The failure came from the budget format's percentage column, which computes
; `100% * display_total[0] / -display_total[1]`.  When display_total[0] is a
; multi-commodity balance (here, 12.00 EUR + 550.00 GBP at Expenses), the
; multiplication against the 100% amount raised a value_error.
;
; The fix (commit c28f1324b, originally for issue #1957) replaced the bare
; scrub() calls in the percentage expression with quantity(), which returns 0
; for multi-commodity balances, and added a zero-guard around the divisor so
; the column prints "0" instead of crashing.  This test uses the exact journal
; from the bug report to confirm the budget report now completes successfully.

~ Monthly
    Expenses:Phone            10.00 GBP
    Expenses:Rent            550.00 GBP
    Assets

2012-01-10 * Phone expense on holidays
    Expenses:Phone            12.00 EUR @@ 10.00 GBP
    Assets:Cash              -10.00 GBP

2012-01-31 * Rent expense
    Expenses:Rent            550.00 GBP
    Assets:Cash             -550.00 GBP

test budget --period 'January 2012' --no-color
 -560.00 GBP  -560.00 GBP            0  100%  Assets
   12.00 EUR
  550.00 GBP   560.00 GBP    12.00 EUR
                            -10.00 GBP     0  Expenses
   12.00 EUR    10.00 GBP    12.00 EUR
                            -10.00 GBP  120%    Phone
  550.00 GBP   550.00 GBP            0  100%    Rent
------------ ------------ ------------ -----
   12.00 EUR
  -10.00 GBP            0    12.00 EUR
                            -10.00 GBP     0
end test

test budget --period 'January 2012' --no-color --flat
 -560.00 GBP  -560.00 GBP            0  100%  Assets
   12.00 EUR    10.00 GBP    12.00 EUR
                            -10.00 GBP  120%  Expenses:Phone
  550.00 GBP   550.00 GBP            0  100%  Expenses:Rent
------------ ------------ ------------ -----
   12.00 EUR
  -10.00 GBP            0    12.00 EUR
                            -10.00 GBP     0
end test
